-- Monsoon Rains Are 15% Below Normal, Indian Meteorological Department Says
-- Abhay Singh
-- 2010-07-20T13:51:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-20/monsoon-rains-are-15-below-normal-indian-meteorological-department-says.html

          
          
             India’s monsoon, the main source of
irrigation for the nation’s 235 million farmers, was 15 percent
below normal as of today, the weather office said.  
 The nation received 298.3 millimeters of rain in the June
1-July 20 period, compared with the 50-year average of 350.4
millimeters, the India Meteorological Department said on its
website. The monsoon was 16 percent below normal in June.  
 Rainfall was 15 percent below normal in northwest India,
including Uttar Pradesh state, and 19 percent below average in
central states including Madhya Pradesh, the agency said.  
          
          


  


        